Overall Progress
Day 100 represents much more than another study session—it marks one hundred consecutive days of consistent effort. Compared to the beginning of this journey, your Spanish has shifted from translating isolated words to producing complete thoughts and holding natural travel conversations. Many of your core phrases now come automatically, allowing you to focus more on communicating than on constructing each sentence. The new weekly phrases are already beginning to stick, and Lesson 12 introduces another layer of useful conversational vocabulary that will continue strengthening your confidence. Maintaining this level of consistency while balancing work, the gym, travel planning, your cookbook project, your new travel-agent training, and family responsibilities is a significant accomplishment.
